tle=2016 MAMA Nominees|url=http://mama.mwave.me/nominees|accessdate=January 31, 2019|work=Mnet Asian Music Awards|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161029164131/http://mama.mwave.me/nominees|archivedate=October 29, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Mnet Asian Music Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]]\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |  2017\n| Best Band Performance\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \"I Smile\"\n| {{nominated}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://enter.etoday.co.kr/view/news_view.php?varAtcId=128727|title=[2017 MAMA] \ud601\uc624, \ubca0\uc2a4\ud2b8 \ubc34\ub4dc \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4\uc0c1 \"\uc7ac\ubc0c\ub294 \uac78 \uba4b\uc9c0\uac8c \uc624\ub798\"|work=Biz Enter|language=ko|date=December 1, 2017|access-date=January 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Song of the Year\n| {{nominated}}\n| <ref>{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wu8Pu11nM8s|title=[2017 MAMA] Song of the Year Nominees|website=YouTube|publisher=Mnet K-POP|accessdate=January 31, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2018\n| Best Band Performance\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \"Shoot Me\"\n| {{nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.axs.com/2018-mnet-asian-music-awards-mama-complete-list-of-nominees-134882|title=2018 Mnet Asian Music Awards (MAMA): Complete list of nominees|work=AXS Contributor|date=November 12, 2018|access-date=January 31, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Song of the Year\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n| rowspan=1 |2019\n|Best Band Performance\n| rowspan=\"1\" |\"Time Of Our Life\"\n| {{nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.businesstimes.cn/articles/120907/20191026/2019-mama-unveils-official-nominees-voting-open.htm|title='2019 MAMA' Unveils Official Nominees, Check the List and Voting Here|last=Times|first=Business|date=2019-10-26|website=Business Times|access-date=2019-11-10}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center; background:#f4f4ff;\"|'''[[Seoul Music Awards]]'''\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | 2016\n| Bonsang Award\n| rowspan=3 | Day6\n| {{nominated}}\n| rowspan=3 | <ref>{{cite web|title=Seoul Music Awards Global (scroll to K-POP STAR 2015 [LIVE VOTE] and click \"Main, Popular (Overseas) and Rookie\" to reveal the nominees)|url=http://seoulmusicawards.com/global.html|website=Seoul Music Awards|publisher=SportsSeoul|accessdate=December 9, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208102244/http://www.seoulmusicawards.com/global.html|archivedate=December 8, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| New Artist Award\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n| Popularity Award\n| {{nominated}}\n|}\n\n==Fan club==\nThe official fan club's name is 'My Day'. This is the name that was finally chosen due to the fans' ideas and votes in line with the release date of the first regular album \"SUNRISE\" on June 7, 2017. It means \"Day6\" and \"Fans\" are precious things that can fill each other's day. The song 'My Day' was released in February 2017 in 'Every DAY 6 February' and is considered a fan song.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvdaily.asiae.co.kr/read.php3?aid=15148797901312053010|title=\ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4, \uacf5\uc2dd \ud32c\ud074\ub7fd 1\uae30 '\ub9c8\uc774\ub370\uc774' \ucc3d\ub2e8|website=tvdaily.asiae.co.kr}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Day6}}\n* [http://day6.jype.com Day6 Official Website]\n\n{{Day6}}\n{{JYP Entertainment}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:2015 establishments in South Korea]]\n[[Category:JYP Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:K-pop music groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Seoul]]\n[[Category:South Korean boy bands]]\n[[Category:South Korean dance music groups]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop rock music groups]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = DAY6\n| image           = \n| image size      = \n| caption         = DAY6 band members, 2019<br />From left to right: Wonpil, Jae, Young K, Dowoon, Sungjin.\n| background      = group_or_band\n| landscape       = yes\n| alias           = \n| origin          = [[Seoul, South Korea]]\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[pop rock]]|[[alternative rock]]|[[pop punk]]| [[power pop]]}}\n| years_active    = {{start date|2015}}\u2013present\n| label           = {{Flatlist|\n* [[Studio J]]\n* [[Warner Music Group|Warner Japan]]}}\n| associated_acts = [[JYP Nation]]\n| website         = *{{URL|day6.jype.com}}(Korea)\n*{{URL|http://day6japan.com}} (Japan)\n| current_members = *[[Jae Park|Jae]]\n*Sungjin\n*[[Young K]]\n*Wonpil\n*Dowoon\n| past_members    = Junhyeok\n}}\n'''DAY6''' ({{ko-hhrm|\ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4|hanja=|mr=|rr=De-i-sik-seu}}) is a South Korean band under the label [[JYP Entertainment]]. The group marked their debut on September 7, 2015 with [[Extended play|EP]] ''[[The Day (EP)|The Day]],'' which peaked at No.2 on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'}}s [[Billboard Charts|World Album Chart]] a week following its release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sg.celebrity.yahoo.com/day6-ranks-second-on-billboard-world-album-chart-084410505.html|title=DAY6 Ranks Second on Billboard World Album Chart|website=sg.celebrity.yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-27}}</ref> The band consists of five members: Sungjin, [[Jae Park|Jae]], [[Young K]], Wonpil, and Dowoon. Originally a six-piece band, DAY6 became a quintet after keyboardist Junhyeok left in February 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/827167wpp/day6s-junhyeok-withdraws-from-group-and-contract-with-jype|title=DAY6\u2019s Junhyeok Withdraws From Group and Contract With JYPE|date=Feb 27, 2016 |website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2019-12-27}}</ref> All of the DAY6 members are majorly involved in writing, composing and producing the band's music.{{short description|South Korean band}}\nDAY6 has been known to not pertain to any genre boundary. Such reputation was proven largely by their year-long project ''Every DAY6'' in 2017, wherein the band would release two songs every month of the year. By the end of the project, 25 songs were added to their discography, genres of which ranged from hard rock and upbeat sing-a-longs to mellow ballads. Their first full-length album ''[[Sunrise (Day6 album)|Sunrise]],'' consisted of songs released in the first half of the ''Every DAY6'' project, was number 14 on [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard's]] ''The 25 Greatest K-Pop Albums of the 2010s: Staff List,''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8546586/greatest-k-pop-albums-2010s-top-25|title=The 25 Greatest K-Pop Albums of the 2010s: Staff List|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-12-27}}</ref> and the project kick-off song \"I Wait\" was placed No.81 on [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard's]] ''The 100 Greatest K-Pop Songs of the 2010s: Staff List.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8544710/best-k-pop-songs-2010s-top-100|title=The 100 Greatest K-Pop Songs of the 2010s: Staff List|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-12-27}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n===2014\u20132016: Formation, debut with ''The Day'', Junhyeok\u2019s departure and ''Daydream''===\nJYP Entertainment initially announced the debut of a five-member band called 5LIVE, composed of Sungjin, [[Jae Park|Jae]], [[Young K]], Junhyeok, and Wonpil. In 2014, the band began promotions with appearing on the fourth episode of [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s reality-survival program ''Who is Next: Win'' and releasing a song titled \"Lovely Girl\" as part of the original soundtrack of 2013 TV series ''[[Bel Ami (TV series)|Bel Ami]]''.<ref name=predebut>{{cite web|last1=Yoon|first1=Sung-yul|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] JYP, \uc5ed\ub300\uae09\ubbf8\ubaa8 \u65b0\uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ucd9c\uaca9..'\ub0b4\ub144 \uc0c1\ubc18\uae30\u00b76\uc778\uc870'|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2013121908272999223&type=3|website=StarNews|accessdate=September 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn mid-2015, drummer Dowoon joined the line-up and the band was renamed DAY6.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Eun-ae|title=JYP \"6\uc778\uc870 \ubcf4\uc774\ubc34\ub4dc \ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4 \uc900\ube44 \uc911\u2026\ub370\ubdd4\uc2dc\uae30 \ubbf8\uc815\"|url=http://stoo.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?sec=enter5&idxno=2015073113192796630|website=Sports Today|publisher=stoo.com|accessdate=September 4, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160724234301/http://stoo.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?sec=enter5&idxno=2015073113192796630|archive-date=July 24, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nDAY6 released their debut [[extended play|EP]], ''[[The Day (Day6 EP)|The Day]]'', with the lead single \"Congratulations\" on September 7, 2015, marking their debut.<ref name=debut1>{{cite web|last1=Jang|first1=So-jin|title=JYP, \uccab \ubc34\ub4dc \ucd9c\uaca9\u2026\ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4(DAY6) \uc624\ub294 6\uc77c \ub370\ubdd4|url=http://sports.khan.co.kr/news/sk_index.html?cat=view&art_id=201509021351193&sec_id=540301|website=Sports Kyunghyang|publisher=The Kyunghyang Shinmun|accessdate=September 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name=debut2>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Jae-hyun|title=JYP, \uccab \ub0a8\uc131 \ubc34\ub4dc '\ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4'\u2026\ub370\ubdd4 \uc568\ubc94 '\ub354 \ub370\uc774'|url=http://www.newsis.com/ar_detail/view.html?ar_id=NISX20150902_0010262687&cID=10601&pID=10600|website=NEWSIS|publisher=NEWSIS|accessdate=September 4, 2015}}</ref> The album charted at No.2 on [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard's]] World Album Chart a week following its release.\n\nDAY6 held their first live concert ''D-Day'' for 2 nights in November 21\u201322, 2015 at YES24 MUVhall. Aside from performing songs from their debut album, the band also did multiple covers and played some unreleased materials of theirs.\n\nOn December 5, 2015, DAY6 held their first overseas fanmeeting in [[Singapore]] at the Marina Bay Sands Convention Centre.\n\nOn February 27, 2016, JYP Entertainment stated that Junhyeok had departed from the band due to personal reasons and terminated his contract with the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.instiz.net/pt/3619876|title=[\uc778\ud2f0\ud3ec\ud138] JYP\ubc34\ub4dc \ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4 \uba64\ubc84 \uc900\ud601 \uacf5\uc2dd \ud0c8\ud1f4|website=\uc778\uc2a4\ud2f0\uc988(instiz, \u97f3\u601d\u63d0\u8d44)}}</ref> DAY6 remained as a five-member band.\n\nOn March 30, 2016, DAY6 released their second EP, ''[[Daydream (EP)|Daydream]]'', with the title track \"Letting Go\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2016/03/29/day6-is-letting-go-by-rocking-out-in-comeback-mv/|title=DAY6 Is \"Letting Go\" and Rocking Out in Comeback MV - Soompi|website=www.soompi.com}}</ref> On March 31, DAY6 made their official stage debut on the music program ''[[M Countdown]]'', six months after their initial debut. Following the release, the band held their second live concert ''Dream'' for 2 nights on May 28\u201329, 2016 at YES24 Live Hall, and one night overseas in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]] at the Thunder Dome.\n\n===2017: ''Every DAY6'' Project===\nOn December 29, 2016, DAY6 announced their upcoming monthly project in 2017 titled ''Every DAY6'', in which the band would release two songs every month on the sixth (except May, June, August, and October) along with concerts prior to the song's release, music videos, and 4 fixed [[V Live (website)|VLIVEs]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/277586/20170103/day6-release-teaser-images-for-every-day6-january.htm|title=DAY6 release teaser images for 'Every DAY6 January'|last=KpopStarz|date=2017-01-03|work=KpopStarz|access-date=2017-04-10}}</ref> \n\nDAY6 released their first monthly single with the release of lead single \"I Wait\" and sidetrack \"Goodbye Winter\" on January 6, 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=DAY6, 2017 JYP \uccab \ucef4\ubc31\uc8fc\uc790\u2026\uc624\ub294 6\uc77c \uc2e0\uace1\ubc1c\ud45c|url=http://joynews.inews24.com/php/news_view.php?g_menu=700300&g_serial=999539|accessdate=2017-01-02|agency=joy news|date=2017-01-02|language=ko}}</ref> Their second monthly single was released with the lead single  \"You Were Beautiful\" and sidetrack \"My Day\" on February 6.<ref>{{cite news|title=DAY6, 2\uc6d4 \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8\uc1a1 6\uc77c \ubc1c\ud45c\u2026\uc774\ubcc4\uac10\uc131 '\uc608\ubee4\uc5b4'|url=http://news.jtbc.joins.com/article/article.aspx?news_id=NB11411691|accessdate=2017-02-02|agency=JTBC News|date=2017-01-31|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nTheir third monthly single with the lead single \"How Can I Say\" and sidetrack \"I Would\" was released on March 6. They also promoted on the music program ''[[M Countdown]]'' on March 9.<ref>{{Citation|last=Mnet K-POP|title=[DAY6 \u2013 How Can I Say] Comeback Stage {{!}}  M COUNTDOWN 170309 EP.514|date=2017-03-09|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JRle7GfLFAQ|accessdate=2017-04-10}}</ref> Their fourth monthly single consisting of the lead single  \"I'm Serious\" and sidetrack \"Say Wow\" was released on April 6. They also promoted on the music program ''[[M Countdown]]'' the same day. Their fifth monthly single was released on May 8, with the lead single \"Dance Dance\" and sidetrack \"Man in a Movie\".<ref>{{cite news|title=\"\uc2e0\ub098\uac8c \ub180\uc544\ubcf4\uc790\" \ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4, 5\uc6d4 \uc2e0\uace1 \u2018\ub304\uc2a4 \ub304\uc2a4\u2019 \uacf5\uac1c\n|url=http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0002917946|accessdate=2017-05-20|work=naver|date=2017-05-08|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2017, DAY6 released their first full-length album, ''[[Sunrise (Day6 album)|Sunrise]]'', with a total of 14 tracks. It consists of the releases from January to May, the rebooted version of \"Letting Go\", the final version of \"Congratulations\", <ref>{{Cite news |url=http://daily.hankooki.com/lpage/entv/201705/dh20170530132643139050.htm |title=DAY6, \uccab \uc815\uaddc\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4 \uc18c\uc2dd\uacfc \ud568\uaed8 \ud2f0\uc800 \uc774\ubbf8\uc9c0 \uacf5\uac1c '\ud32c\ub4e4 \ud658\ud638' |date=2017-05-30|accessdate=2017-05-30|work=Daily Korea|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.soompi.com/2017/06/06/day6-teases-upcoming-full-album-sunrise-spoiler-video/|title=Listen : DAY6 Teases Upcoming Full Album \"Sunrise\" With Spoiler Video|last=soompi|date=2017-06-06|work=soompi|access-date=2017-06-19}}</ref> and two new tracks: \"I Smile\" (the lead single of the album) and \"Lean On Me\". Day6 also  announced their official fanclub name, \"My Day\", the same day.<ref>{{cite web|title=DAY6 \ud32c\ud074\ub7fd\uba85 \ud22c\ud45c \uc548\ub0b4|url=https://fans.jype.com/BoardView?BoardName=DAY6_Notice&Num=163|publisher=fans.jype|accessdate=2017-06-07|language=ko|date=2017-06-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.soompi.com/2017/06/07/day6-announces-official-fan-club-name/|title=Day6 Announces Official Fan Club Name After Comeback|last=soompi|date=2017-06-07|work=soompi|access-date=2017-06-19}}</ref>\n\nTheir July single consisting of the lead single \"Hi Hello\" and sidetrack \"Be Lazy\" was released on July 6. Their August single consisting of the lead single \"What Can I Do\" and sidetrack \"Whatever!\" released on August 7.<ref>{{cite news|title=DAY6, \uc624\ub298(7\uc77c) 8\uc6d4 \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \uac00\ub3d9\u2026\ud574\uc678 \uc9c4\ucd9c\uae4c\uc9c0|url=http://news.jtbc.joins.com/article/article.aspx?news_id=NB11504437|accessdate=2017-08-08|agency=jtbc News|date=2017-08-07|language=ko}}</ref> Their September single with the lead single \"I Loved You\" and sidetrack \"I'll Remember\" released on September 6.<ref>{{cite news|author1=\ucd5c\uc815\ubbfc|title=\ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4 \uc81c\uc774, \uc2e0\uace1 \u2018\uc544\uc774 \ub7ec\ube0c\ub4dc \uc720\u2019 \ud2f0\uc800 \uacf5\uac1c\ud150\uc544\uc2dc\uc544|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1284826|accessdate=2017-09-02|work=\ud150\uc544\uc2dc\uc544|date=2017-09-01|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author1=\uc815\uc9c0\uc6d0|title=[Oh!\uc388 \ucef7] \ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4 Jae, \uc548\uacbd \ubc97\uace0 \ubbf8\uc18c\ub144 \ub9e4\ub825\u2026'\ud48b\ud48b \ube44\uc8fc\uc5bc'|url=http://www.koreadaily.com/news/read.asp?art_id=5558409|accessdate=2017-09-02|agency=Korea Daily|date=2017-08-31|language=ko}}</ref> Day6 originally would released their October single on October 7 and later installment to released on September 29, which consists of the lead single \"When You Love Someone\" and the sidetrack \"I Need Somebody\". The music videos of their August, September, and October singles were a three-part story about high school friendship and love.\n\nDAY6 held their North American meet and greet tour, DAY6 Live & Meet in North America 2017, hosted by SubKulture Entertainment. The tour started in Los Angeles on October 20, Austin on October 22, New York on October 24, Detroit on October 27, and stopped in Toronto on October 29.<ref>https://www.soompi.com/2017/08/25/day6-announces-dates-locations-2017-north-american-meet-greet-tour/</ref>\n\nTheir November single consisting of the lead single \"All Alone\" and sidetrack \"Pouring\" was released on November 6. On November 28, JYP Entertainment announced the band's first nationwide tour in 2018, Every DAY6 Concert Nationwide Tour. The tour started in Busan on January 20\u201321, Daegu on January 27 and stopped in Daejeon on February 10.<ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003670208</ref><ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003190905</ref>\n\nOn December 6, DAY6 official concluded their monthly project with the releases of their second full-length album, ''[[Moonrise (Day6 album)|Moonrise]]''. The album contained the previous releases from July to November, the title track \"I Like You\", two sidetrack (\"Better Better\" and \"I'll Try\"), and the final versions of the B-sides from the debut mini album ''[[The Day (Day6 EP)|The Day]]''.<ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000296243</ref>\n\n===2018: ''Youth'' series, Japanese debut and first world tour===\nDAY6 official announced the recruitment of their first generation fan club from January 5 to January 25.<ref>https://www.soompi.com/2018/01/03/day6-announces-details-first-official-fan-club-recruitment/</ref>\n\nDAY6 announced would made their official debut in Japan on March 14 with their first Japanese single, \"[[If -Mata Aetara-|If \uff5e\u307e\u305f\u9022\u3048\u305f\u3089\uff5e]]\". The single also serves as theme song for the Japanese drama ''Repeat''.<ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000304309</ref><ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003695945</ref> The music video for the single was released on February 2.<ref>http://day6japan.com/news/detail/6</ref>\n\nDAY6 held their Every Day6 Finale Concert - The Best Moments on March 3 and March 4 in the Olympic Hall.<ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000315877</ref>\n\nIn April 2018, DAY6 announced their first Japanese concert, DAY6 1st Live in Japan 'The Best Day' on June 13 at Tsutaya O-East in Tokyo.<ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003754479</ref><ref>http://day6japan.com/news/detail/44</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, it was announced that DAY6 would release their second Japanese single, \"Stop the Rain\", on July 25, which was produced by Japanese guitarist Ubukata Shinichi (member of ELLEGARDEN and Nothing's Carved In Stone).<ref>http://day6japan.com/news/detail/53</ref><ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=382&aid=0000645446</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, DAY6 released their first [[greatest hits album]] in Japan, ''[[The Best Day (Day6 album)|The Best Day]]'', which is composed of the band's previous Korean singles and three new-version tracks: \"Congratulations\" (English Ver.), \"I Wait\" (Japanese Ver.), and \"You Were Beautiful\" (English Ver.).\n\nOn June 26, DAY6 released their third EP ''[[Shoot Me: Youth Part 1]]''.<ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=021&aid=0002357331</ref><ref>http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=469&aid=0000309821</ref> The mini album contains seven tracks, with the lead single titled \"Shoot Me\". The second part, ''[[Remember Us: Youth Part 2]]'', was released on December 10 with the title track \"days gone by\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201811231024466862420_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Day6 to drop new album in December|language=|work=K-POP Herald|accessdate=November 29, 2018}}</ref> On October 17, 2018, between the release of the two parts, their first Japanese studio album ''[[Unlock (album)|Unlock]]'' was released.\n\nDAY6 went on their first world tour, titled ''Youth'', subsequently performing in 24 cities in Asia, Australia, North America and Europe from June 22, 2018, to January 29, 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/topic/1076271/1076271/read?oid=109&aid=0003919450|title=[\uc778\ud130\ubdf0\u2462] \ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4 \"\uc62c\ud574 '\ud589\ubcf5\ud55c \ub0a0\ub4e4\uc774\uc5c8\ub2e4'..\uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4 \ud55c\uad6d\uc5b4 \ub5bc\ucc3d \uac10\ub3d9\"|work=OSEN|publisher=Naver|language=ko|date=December 11, 2018|access-date=January 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2019\u2014present: ''The Book of Us'' series and second world tour===\nOn January 10, 2019, the DAY6 YouTube account announced that recruitment for their second-generation fan club would begin that month.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cKxGlYjMC7A</ref>\n\nDAY6 released their fifth extended play ''[[The Book of Us: Gravity]]'' on July 15, 2019. They received their first-ever [[Music programs of South Korea|music show]] win on July 24.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201907251045251977808_1|title=DAY6, \ub370\ubdd4 \uccab \uc74c\ubc29 1\uc704...\"\ud32c\ub4e4\uacfc \ud568\uaed8 \uc4f4 \ud55c \ud398\uc774\uc9c0, \uc18c\uc911\ud788 \uac04\uc9c1\ud560 \uac83\" \ubb49\ud074 \uc18c\uac10|work=Herald Corporation|date=July 25, 2019|accessdate=July 25, 2019|language=ko}}</ref> They embarked on their second world tour ''Gravity'' on August 9.<ref>{{cite web|first=Chae-yoon|last=Lee|url=http://viewers.heraldcorp.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=38510|title=[\uac00\uc694 \uba54\ubaa8] \ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4, 7\uc6d4 15\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31+2019 \uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4 \uc608\uace0|work=Herald Corp|date=July 1, 2019|accessdate=July 1, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nOn October 22, they released their third Korean-language studio album, ''[[The Book of Us: Entropy]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20191022008900315|title=DAY6 returns with 3rd full album 'The Book of Us: Entropy'|last=Park|first=Boram|date=October 22, 2019|work=Yonhap News Agency|access-date=October 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n===Current members===\n* [[Jae Park|Jae]] (\uc81c\uc774) \u2013 lead guitarist, lead vocalist<ref name=ThaiPR />\n*Sungjin (\uc131\uc9c4) \u2013 leader, main vocalist, rhythm guitarist<ref name=ThaiPR>{{cite web |title=DAY6 The 1st Live & Meet in Bangkok 2015 |url=http://www.thaipr.net/entertain/655933 |date=October 16, 2015 |publisher=BeUS Production |via=ThaiPR.net |accessdate=November 29, 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Young K]] (\uc601\ucf00\uc774) \u2013  bassist, lead vocalist<ref name=ThaiPR/> \n*Wonpil (\uc6d0\ud544) \u2013 synthesizer, keyboardist, lead vocalist<ref name=ThaiPR />\n*Dowoon (\ub3c4\uc6b4) \u2013 drummer<ref name=ThaiPR/>\n\n===Former members===\n*Junhyeok (\uc900\ud601) \u2013 keyboardist, vocalist<ref name=ThaiPR/>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|Day6 discography}}\n<!--Studio albums only. Everything else should go on the discography page.-->\n* ''[[Sunrise (Day6 album)|Sunrise]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Moonrise (Day6 album)|Moonrise]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Unlock (album)|Unlock]]'' (2018)\n* ''[[The Book of Us: Entropy]]'' (2019)\n==Tours and concerts==\n{{Main|List of Day6 concert tours}}\n\n===Headlining concerts===\n* Day6 Live Concert \"D-Day\" (2015)\n* Day6 Live Concert \"Dream\" (2016)\n* Every DAY6 Concerts (2017\u20132018)\n* Day6 1st Live in Japan \"The Best Day\" (2018)\n* Day6 Christmas Special Concert \"The Present\" (2018, 2019)\n\n===Headlining tours===\n* Day6 First World Tour \"Youth\" (2018-2019)\n* Day6 2nd Live Tour in Japan (2018)\n* Day6 2nd World Tour \"Gravity\" (2019-2020)\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Note(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | {{abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2016\n| ''DAY6's Free Radio'' (season 1)\n| 10 episodes\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201611011915061483725_1|title='V\uc571' DAY6, Jae\uc640 \uc6d0\ud544\uc758 \ub77c\ub514\uc624DJ \ub3c4\uc804\uae30|work=Herald Pop|language=ko|date=November 1, 2016|access-date=January 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2017\n| ''[Tour Avatar] DAY6 x GYEONGJU'' \n| Ep. 7 & 8\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.arirang.com/Tv2/TVCommon_NoStaff_Archive.asp?sys_lang=Eng&PROG_CODE=TVCR0828&MENU_CODE=102535&view_seq=23209&cnt=1|title=Tour Avatar Ep.08 - GYEONGJU|language=en|website=Arirang|access-date=July 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2018\n| ''DAY6's Free Radio'' (season 2)\n| 5 episodes (+ 1 special clip)\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vlive.tv/search/all?query=DAY6\uc758+Free\ud55c+\ub77c\ub514\uc624+\uc2dc\uc98c2|title=DAY6's Free Radio \u2013 Season 2|language=ko|website=V LIVE|access-date=January 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2018\n| ''Stark Idol League DAY6'' \n| 4 episodes \n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/i/moments/1025246001630609408|title=STARK IDOL LEAGUE DAY6|language=ko|website=Twitter|access-date=July 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2019\n| ''DAY6 Real Trip <DAYOFF> in Jeju''\n| 6 episodes (+ 2 special clips)\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/?ac=article_view&entry_id=1064731|title=DAY6, \uafc8\uac19\uc740 \uc81c\uc8fc \ud734\uac00 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026\ub370\ubdd4 \ud6c4 \uccab \ub9ac\uc5bc\ub9ac\ud2f0 '\ub370\uc774\uc624\ud504' \uc120\uc0ac|work=Xport News|language=ko|date=January 14, 2019|access-date=January 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"