{"title_page": "Walter Taylor (footballer)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Walter Taylor\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = \n| birth_date = 1901\n| birth_place = [[Manchester]], England\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = \n| position = [[Outside forward|Outside right]]\n| youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = {{0|000}}?\u20131921 |clubs1 = [[New Mills A.F.C.|New Mills]]               |caps1 =   |goals1 = \n| years2 = 1921\u20131922       |clubs2 = [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] |caps2 = 1 |goals2 = 0\n}}\n'''Walter Taylor''' (1901\u2013?) was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played as an [[outside forward|outside right]]. Born in [[Manchester]], he played for [[New Mills A.F.C.|New Mills]] and [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], who signed him for a fee of \u00a325 in December 1921. After just two weeks with the club, he made his [[English Football League|Football League]] debut on 2 January 1922, in a 3\u20130 defeat away to [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]. It was his only appearance for Manchester United, and he was released on a free transfer in April 1922.<ref>{{cite book |first=Garth |last=Dykes |title=The United Alphabet: A Complete Who's Who of Manchester United F.C. |year=1994 |publisher=ACL & Polar Publishing |location=Leicester |isbn=0-9514862-6-8 |page=371 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.stretfordend.co.uk/playermenu/taylor_w.html Profile] at StretfordEnd.co.uk\n*[http://www.mufcinfo.com/manupag/a-z_player_archive/a-z_player_archive_pages/taylor_walter.html Profile] at MUFCInfo.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Taylor, Walter}}\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Manchester United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:New Mills A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-forward-1900s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Walter Taylor\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = \n| birth_date = {{birth year|1901}}\n| birth_place = [[Manchester]], England\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = \n| position = [[Outside forward|Outside right]]\n| youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = {{0|000}}?\u20131921 |clubs1 = [[New Mills A.F.C.|New Mills]]               |caps1 =   |goals1 = \n| years2 = 1921\u20131922       |clubs2 = [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] |caps2 = 1 |goals2 = 0\n}}\n'''Walter Taylor''' (1901\u2013?) was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played as an [[outside forward|outside right]]. Born in [[Manchester]], he played for [[New Mills A.F.C.|New Mills]] and [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], who signed him for a fee of \u00a325 in December 1921. After just two weeks with the club, he made his [[English Football League|Football League]] debut on 2 January 1922, in a 3\u20130 defeat away to [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]. It was his only appearance for Manchester United, and he was released on a free transfer in April 1922.<ref>{{cite book |first=Garth |last=Dykes |title=The United Alphabet: A Complete Who's Who of Manchester United F.C. |year=1994 |publisher=ACL & Polar Publishing |location=Leicester |isbn=0-9514862-6-8 |page=371 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.stretfordend.co.uk/playermenu/taylor_w.html Profile] at StretfordEnd.co.uk\n*[http://www.mufcinfo.com/manupag/a-z_player_archive/a-z_player_archive_pages/taylor_walter.html Profile] at MUFCInfo.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Taylor, Walter}}\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Manchester United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:New Mills A.F.C. players]]\n\n\n[[Category:Association football forwa